Set environment variables before executing script
 * PREFIX to identify location of C:\maintenance
 * MAINTENANCEPATH to identify location of scripts
 * LOGFILE to identify logfile
 * PATH - include C:\maintenance\libexec or something like that in path

Watchdog timer
 * Kill maintenance script if watchdog timer exceeded
 * Provide a utility to extend watchdog timer
  (used by a maintenance script that's about to execute a command
   which is known to take quite a bit of time)
